ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: When you use social media, how often do you - Feel creative because of something you expressed, posted, or shared?
When you use social media, how often do you - Feel proud of yourself because of something you expressed, posted, or shared?
When you use social media, how often do you - Feel hurt by a negative interaction (e.g., comment, post, DM) with someone?
When you use social media, how often do you - Feel more connected to your friends?
When you use social media, how often do you - Feel left out or excluded by friends or people you know?
When you use social media, how often do you - Feel supported and encouraged by your friends or people you know?
When you use social media, how often do you - Feel disappointed about not getting enough responses (likes, comments, views, or shares)?
When you use social media, how often do you - Feel pressure to show the best version of yourself?
When you use social media, how often do you - Feel happy because of a positive interaction (e.g., comment, post, DM) with someone?
When you use social media, how often do you - Feel like other people are doing better than you?
When you use social media, how often do you - Feel worried that you are missing out on things?
When you use social media, how often do you - Feel like you are enjoying yourself and having fun?
When you use social media, how often do you - Feel nervous when you are waiting for someone to respond?
When you use social media, how often do you - Feel pressure to be available to others (e.g., respond right away)?
When you use social media, how often do you - Feel stressed or nervous about something you see online?
When you use social media, how often do you - Feel like you are accepted for who you are?
When you use social media, how often do you - Feel upset or bad about yourself compared to other people your age (such as in appearance, accomplishments,  relationships, or other things)?

When you use social media, how often do you - Feel happy or good about yourself compared to other people your age (such as in appearance, accomplishments, relationships, social status, or other things)?
When you use social media, how often do you - Feel excited or happy that you got likes, comments, views, or shares on your posts?
When you use social media, how often do you - Feel uncertain about how others will respond to the things you post on social media?
When you use social media, how often do you - Feel out of control about how much time you spend on social media?
When you use social media, how often do you - Feel frustrated by other people posting things to appear a certain way on social media?
When you use social media, how often do you - Feel overwhelmed by the number of things you need to look at or respond to on social media?
When you use social media, how often do you - Feel that social media has a NEGATIVE impact on your mood?
When you use social media, how often do you - Feel that social media has a POSITIVE impact on your mood?
